---
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
import Container from "@components/Container.astro";
import Link from "@components/Link.astro";
import { ABOUT } from "@consts";
---

<Layout title={ABOUT.TITLE} description={ABOUT.DESCRIPTION}>
  <Container>
    <div class="animate space-y-6">
      <h1 class="font-semibold text-black dark:text-white">About</h1>
      <article>
        <p>
          I'm a software engineer at <Link href="https://www.ibm.com/z" external
            >IBM</Link
          > in New York City, working on test automation and technology modernization
          for the IBM Z mainframe platform. My day-to-day involves bringing modern
          open-source tools — Go, Python, Locust, Grafana k6 — to z/OS environments.
        </p>
        <p>
          I'm pursuing an M.S. in Computer Engineering at <Link
            href="https://engineering.nyu.edu/"
            external>NYU Tandon School of Engineering</Link
          >
          and a B.A. in Computer Science and Theater from <Link
            href="https://www.wesleyan.edu/"
            external>Wesleyan University</Link
          >, where I was a <Link
            href="https://www.wesleyan.edu/patricelli/"
            external>Patricelli Center Fellow</Link
          >.
        </p>
        <p>
          Outside of work, I build tools at the intersection of geospatial AI
          and humanitarian use. My project
          <Link href="https://github.com/msradam/dream-meridian" external
            >DreamMeridian</Link
          > — which runs AI-powered geospatial queries entirely offline on a Raspberry
          Pi for refugee camps and disaster zones — placed 2nd out of 1,600+ participants
          in the ARM AI Developer Challenge. I was also
          <Link
            href="https://engineering.nyu.edu/news/meet-adam-munawar-rahman-leveraging-ai-humanitarian-use"
            external>profiled by NYU Tandon Engineering</Link
          >
          for this work.
        </p>
        <p>
          This thread runs back to my time at UNICEF, where I built geospatial
          routing tools for school site planning, and through projects like <Link
            href="/projects">AskStreets</Link
          > (GraphRAG for urban planning) and our climate-aware emergency routing
          tool for Brownsville, Brooklyn, which won Best Community Communication
          Tool at the LEAP Climate Hackathon at the American Museum of Natural History.
        </p>
        <p>
          I'm also a theatermaker. I've produced 34 shows, directed Ayad
          Akhtar's <em>Disgraced</em> at Wesleyan, stage-managed <Link
            href="https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/03/theater/really-really-gorgeous-review.html"
            external>Really Really Gorgeous</Link
          > at
          <Link href="https://thetanknyc.org/" external>The Tank NYC</Link>, and
          worked as a sound, set, and <Link href="/design"
            >graphic designer</Link
          >.
        </p>
        <h3>Around the web</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>
            GitHub: <Link href="https://github.com/msradam" external
              >msradam</Link>
          </li>
          <li>
            LinkedIn: <Link href="https://linkedin.com/in/adamsrahman" external
              >adamsrahman</Link>
          </li>
          <li>
            Medium: <Link href="https://medium.com/@msradam" external
              >@msradam</Link>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </Container>
</Layout>
